\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {4.3}{\ignorespaces Monte Carlo distribution of the DNL of the code between two adjacent slicers (out$_0$ and out$_1$), with the $\pm 1$~LSB limits marked.}}{81}{figure.caption.138}%
\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {4.4}{\ignorespaces Quantile-quantile plot of the Monte Carlo threshold spacing deviation against a normal distribution, for the 300 runs of Table~\ref {tab:mc_mismatch}. The near-linear fit ($R^2 = 0.982$, slope $\approx 5.7$~LSB) shows the spacing is close to Gaussian. The target lines at $\pm 2.94\sigma $ are the expected extreme of a 300-sample draw, the normal quantile of $p = 1 - 1/(2N)$ with $N = 300$.}}{82}{figure.caption.139}%
\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {4.5}{\ignorespaces Static characterisation of the synchronous reference: (top) measured transfer function against the ideal staircase, (bottom left) DNL per code and (bottom right) INL per transition.}}{86}{figure.caption.141}%
